ly marked constructions that allow other constituents to appear in the sentence initial position. One of these constructions is ay-inversion. Although it is often labeled a topic-marking construction, it is actually far more versatile. This book aims to explore some of its many facets. The investigation of ay-inversion begins with a survey of its various uses that appear in the data, including some that have to date received very little if any attention in the literature, such as reversed ang-inversion, which combines two of the language’s inversion constructions. Selected observations are then modeled in Role and Reference Grammar and their implications for Tagalog syntax are explored. Finally, the role of ay-inversion in anaphora resolution is investigated and selected processes are modeled in a frame-based account.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aAustronesische Sprachen. 4aMorphosyntax. 4aTagalog. 4aVan Valin, Robert D. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAustronesian Languages.  aInformation Structure.  aMorphosyntax.  aTagalog.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z978311076682008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021 Englishz978311075411708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021z9783110753882oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107555580 cprintz978311075498840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075546640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110755466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110755466/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075411-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021 Englishb20